{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845800506,"sessionID":"ses_2875a3ff6ffeJ8vkKZNGsaUIs0","part":{"id":"prt_d78a5d8e5001256ibp8SZDyLYC","messageID":"msg_d78a5cc08001r4Qb40qhq4YxNr","sessionID":"ses_2875a3ff6ffeJ8vkKZNGsaUIs0","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_9efb52d39ce94a9f8eb4854c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentd codebase","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. The structure of pkg/agentd - find all files and understand the existing code organization\n2. Any existing controllers in the codebase - look for controller patterns, how they're structured\n3. The AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRD types - look in pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/ or similar paths\n4. Any existing cleanup/garbage collection logic in the codebase\n5. How the agentd component is currently structured (main entry point, how components are wired together)\n6. Any existing idle/timeout related logic\n\nSearch in /home/dsj/benchmark for the agentcube project source code. Also check /tmp/agentcube-ref/ if it exists.\n\nReturn:\n- Full file listing of pkg/agentd/\n- Key code patterns for controllers\n- AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter type definitions (especially status fields, conditions, idle-related fields)\n- How components are initialized/wired in agentd\n- Any existing cleanup or garbage collection code","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2875a02eeffeuhfZZXrXl8L4uF (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Here is my complete report:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Analysis: volcano-sh/agentcube\n\n### 1. pkg/agentd/ -- DOES NOT EXIST\n\n**There is no `pkg/agentd/` directory in the codebase.** The `idle-cleanup/design.md` and `idle-cleanup/spec.md` files describe a *planned* `pkg/agentd` package that has not yet been implemented. The design document specifies:\n\n- **Location**: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n- **Binary**: `cmd/agentd/main.go` (also does not exist yet)\n- **Pattern**: A controller-runtime based reconciler for `Sandbox` resources\n- **Purpose**: Idle cleanup controller that deletes Sandboxes after 15 minutes of inactivity\n\nKey design details from `idle-cleanup/design.md`:\n- Uses `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n- Reads annotation `last-activity-time` from Sandbox objects\n- Uses controller-runtime manager pattern (`ctrl.Manager`, `ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy`)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Existing Controller/Reconciler Patterns\n\nThe codebase has a **custom reconciler** (not controller-runtime based) in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/`:\n\n**Files:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/reconciler.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/types.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/sync.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/event_handlers.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/pod.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/metrics.go`\n\n**Pattern summary (`SandboxReconciler`):**\n```go\ntype SandboxReconciler struct {\n    clientset       clientset.Interface\n    informerFactory externalversions.SharedInformerFactory\n    arLister        listers.AgentRuntimeLister\n    ciLister        listers.CodeInterpreterLister\n    podInformer     coreinformers.PodInformer\n    store           Store\n    workqueue       workqueue.RateLimitingInterface\n    workers         int\n    metricsRecorder handler.MetricsRecorder\n    mu              sync.Mutex\n    running         bool\n    stopCh          chan struct{}\n}\n```\n\n- Uses **informers** (SharedInformerFactory) for watching CRs and Pods\n- Uses a **workqueue** with exponential backoff rate limiting\n- **Event handlers** enqueue keys on Add/Update/Delete\n- **syncHandler** dispatches to `reconcileAgentRuntime`, `reconcileCodeInterpreter`, or `reconcilePod`\n- Runs via `Run(stopCh)` method that starts informers, waits for cache sync, then spawns worker goroutines\n\n---\n\n### 3. AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRD Types\n\n**Location**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n\n**AgentRuntime** (`agent_type.go`):\n```go\ntype AgentRuntime struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta\n    metav1.ObjectMeta\n    Spec   AgentRuntimeSpec\n    Status AgentRuntimeStatus\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort\n    Template           *SandboxTemplate\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration   // idle timeout\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration   // TTL\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition  // Only conditions, no idle-specific fields\n}\n```\n\n**CodeInterpreter** (`codeinterpreter_types.go`):\n```go\ntype CodeInterpreter struct {\n    metav1.TypeMeta\n    metav1.ObjectMeta\n    Spec   CodeInterpreterSpec\n    Status CodeInterpreterStatus\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct {\n    Ports              []TargetPort\n    Template           *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate\n    SessionTimeout     *metav1.Duration   // idle timeout\n    MaxSessionDuration *metav1.Duration   // TTL\n    WarmPoolSize       *int32\n    AuthMode           AuthModeType\n}\n\ntype CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n    Conditions []metav1.Condition\n    Ready      bool\n}\n```\n\n**Key observations:**\n- Neither CRD has explicit idle-related status fields\n- `SessionTimeout` and `MaxSessionDuration` are in the **Spec** only\n- Status only has `Conditions` (standard metav1.Condition) and `Ready` (CodeInterpreter only)\n- Idle timeout is communicated via **annotations** on child Sandbox CRs: `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout`\n\n**Shared types** (`shared_types.go`):\n```go\ntype TargetPort struct {\n    PathPrefix string\n    Name       string\n    Port       uint32\n    Protocol   ProtocolType\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing Cleanup/Garbage Collection Logic\n\n**Primary GC implementation**: `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go` -- `LifecycleManager`\n\nThis is a comprehensive garbage collection system with **four cleanup sub-tasks**:\n\n```go\ntype LifecycleManager struct {\n    dynamicClient      dynamic.Interface\n    store              Store\n    checkInterval      time.Duration     // default: 5 minutes\n    defaultTTL         time.Duration     // default: 8 hours\n    defaultIdleTimeout time.Duration     // default: 15 minutes\n    metricsRecorder    MetricsRecorder\n    stopCh             chan struct{}\n}\n```\n\n**GC Cycle** (`runGCCycle`):\n1. **`cleanupExpiredSandboxes`** -- Deletes sandboxes that are:\n   - TTL expired (past `ExpiresAt` or `CreatedAt + defaultTTL`)\n   - Idle expired (`LastActivityAt + defaultIdleTimeout`)\n2. **`cleanupOrphanCRs`** -- Finds CRs (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter) with session-id labels that have no corresponding store entry, and deletes them (limit: 100 per cycle)\n3. **`cleanupGhostEntries`** -- Finds store entries whose corresponding CR no longer exists in the cluster, and cleans them up\n\n**Cleanup reasons (constants)**:\n```go\nGRCleanupReasonTTLExpired = \"ttl_expired\"\nGRCleanupReasonIdle       = \"idle\"\nGRCleanupReasonOrphanCR   = \"orphan_cr\"\nGRCleanupReasonGhostEntry = \"ghost_entry\"\n```\n\n**Idle detection logic**:\n```go\nfunc (m *LifecycleManager) isIdleExpired(info *SandboxInfo, idleTimeout time.Duration, now time.Time) bool {\n    if info.LastActivityAt.IsZero() { return false }\n    if info.Status != \"running\" { return false }\n    return now.After(info.LastActivityAt.Add(idleTimeout))\n}\n```\n\n**API endpoints** provided by LifecycleManager:\n- `GET /sandbox/:sessionID/status` -- Returns sandbox status including `IsIdle`, `TimeToIdle`, `IsExpired`, `TimeToExpiry`\n- `GET /sandboxes` -- List all sandboxes with idle/expiry info\n- `POST /sandbox/:sessionID/extend-ttl` -- Extend sandbox TTL\n\n**Store-level idle support** (`pkg/store/store.go`):\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n```\n\nThe Redis store (`pkg/store/store_redis.go`) implements these using **sorted sets** for efficient range queries:\n- `session:expiry` -- sorted by `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n- `session:last_activity` -- sorted by `LastActivityAt.Unix()`\n\n---\n\n### 5. How Components Are Wired Together\n\nThe project has **two separate binaries/components**:\n\n#### A. PicoD (`cmd/picod/main.go`)\nA lightweight in-sandbox daemon for file operations and command execution:\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    config := picod.ParseFlags()  // --port, --workspace\n    server := picod.NewServer(config)\n    server.Run()\n}\n```\n- Simple Gin HTTP server\n- Routes: `/api/execute`, `/api/files/*`, `/health`\n- No Kubernetes integration\n\n#### B. Router (`pkg/router/server.go`)\nThe main API gateway for agent invocations:\n```go\nfunc NewServer(config *Config) (*Server, error) {\n    jwtManager := NewJWTManager(jwtConfig)\n    storeClient := store.Storage()           // Redis/Valkey singleton\n    sessionManager := NewSessionManager(storeClient)\n    // Registers routes: /v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path\n}\n```\n- Uses `SessionManager` to look up or create sandboxes\n- Proxies requests to sandbox pods via reverse proxy\n- Updates `LastActivityAt` in store on each request\n\n#### C. Workload Manager (no main.go found in workspace)\nThe `pkg/workloadmanager/` package provides:\n- `SandboxReconciler` -- watches CRs and Pods, syncs state to store\n- `LifecycleManager` -- runs GC cycle for cleanup\n- `SandboxCreateHandler` -- HTTP handler for creating sandboxes\n- `SandboxDeleteHandler` -- HTTP handler for deleting sandboxes\n\n**Wiring pattern** (from `sandbox_lifecycle.go`):\n```go\ntype LifecycleManagerDeps struct {\n    DynamicClient      dynamic.Interface\n    Store              Store\n    CheckInterval      time.Duration\n    DefaultTTL         time.Duration\n    DefaultIdleTimeout time.Duration\n    MetricsRecorder    MetricsRecorder\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Existing Idle/Timeout Related Logic\n\n**Summary of all idle/timeout mechanisms:**\n\n| Component | Mechanism | Default | Location |\n|-----------|-----------|---------|----------|\n| **LifecycleManager** | Idle timeout check in GC cycle | 15 min | `handler/constants.go: DefaultIdleTimeout` |\n| **LifecycleManager** | TTL (max duration) check in GC cycle | 8 hours | `handler/constants.go: DefaultSandboxTTL` |\n| **Router Config** | SessionIdleTimeout (config only, not actively used in proxy) | 30 min | `router/config.go` |\n| **Router Config** | SessionMaxDuration (config only) | 24 hours | `router/config.go` |\n| **Router Config** | SessionCheckInterval (config only) | 5 min | `router/config.go` |\n| **Router proxy** | Updates `LastActivityAt` on each request | N/A | `router/proxy.go: handleInvoke` |\n| **Sandbox CR annotation** | `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` | 15 min | `handler/constants.go` |\n| **Sandbox CR annotation** | `last-activity-time` (planned for agentd) | N/A | `idle-cleanup/design.md` |\n| **AgentRuntime Spec** | `SessionTimeout` | N/A (optional) | `apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go` |\n| **AgentRuntime Spec** | `MaxSessionDuration` | N/A (optional) | `apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go` |\n| **CodeInterpreter Spec** | `SessionTimeout` | N/A (optional) | `apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` |\n| **CodeInterpreter Spec** | `MaxSessionDuration` | N/A (optional) | `apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` |\n| **Store (Redis)** | Sorted set for expiry-based queries | N/A | `store/store_redis.go` |\n| **Store (Redis)** | Sorted set for last-activity-based queries | N/A | `store/store_redis.go` |\n\n**Key gap**: The `pkg/agentd` package described in `idle-cleanup/design.md` and `idle-cleanup/spec.md` does **not exist yet**. It is planned to be a controller-runtime based controller that watches Sandbox resources and deletes them based on the `last-activity-time` annotation. The current idle cleanup is handled entirely by the `LifecycleManager` in the workload-manager component, which polls the store rather than watching Kubernetes resources directly.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2875a02eeffeuhfZZXrXl8L4uF","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentd codebase","time":{"start":1775845637390,"end":1775845800503}}}}
